Description: This is a regression package designed to straightforwardly tell you the probabilities of various hypotheses given data, in particular whether a predictor variables affects a predicted variable. In other words, the package gives you the posterior probabilities of hypotheses about model parameters. This is what researchers really want deep down (in their "Bayesian id", Gigerenzer, 2004), but what p-values and all that frequentist garbage cannot provide.
    Continuation lines should be indented. ** FINISH DESCRIPTION **
    I envision the following workflow
    1) Verbally articulate competing hypotheses; collect relevant data
    2) Express your hypotheses in terms of regression model parameters, and specify prior probabilities
    3) Use diagnostic plots to decide on the details of the model (in particular the likelihood used)
    4) Automatically compute all relevant restricted models, obeying the principle of marginality
    5) Compute Bayes factors for the restricted and full models
    6) Use these Bayes factors and the prior probabilities of hypotheses about model parameters to compute posterior probabilities of model parameters
